function keep_only_names(words)
    return filter(word -> startswith(word, uppercase:firstbyte(word))), words)
end
```

This function filters the input `words` list by keeping only those words that start with a capital letter. It uses the `filter` function and the `startswith` function to check if a word starts with an uppercase letter. The `uppercase:firstbyte(word)` is used to convert the first character of the word to its uppercase equivalent, which is then compared with the first byte of the original word.
